9:
Wow, this is deep! But I think I'm
finally getting it!
13:
Never thought I'd meet a noisy
reader, but I'm not surprised it's you.
16:
Since things have calmed down a
little, I thought we could relax and
have a drink... But am I interrupting?
20:
Come on, Bro! You know I wouldn't
say no to that!
37:
Heh... I can feel the guilt and fatigue
from an afternoon drink melting
away already...
40:
Seriously? Afternoon's the best time
for it.
44:
Drinking on an empty stomach is
bad for the body, you two.
48:
Well, if it isn't the wolf who's always
too busy to say hi!
53:
I brought some jerky for us to snack
on, but perhaps that was
unnecessary?
58:
Nobody's gonna say no to free
snacks.
63:
This... kotatsu thing...
I'm beginning to understand the
appeal...
67:
Your ears are drooping more than
usual. What's up? You tired too?
76: ...It's happened to you as well, has it?
82:
The hell is this? Portraits of catfolk
and dogfolk women...
92:
It's no laughing matter, Bro! They
just won't let up!
96:
I've got hundreds of these things
now! What am I supposed to do?!
102:
Our prominent political positions
seem to have attracted attention of
all kinds.
106:
Doesn't sound too bad to me. Surely
one or two ladies have caught your
eye?
112: If only it were that simple...
118:
It is likely that many of them are
agents working to undo the
progress our societies have made.
Our peoples could be back at war
before we knew it.
127:
We're both too busy right now
anyway, so we're going to turn
everyone down.
131:
By the way, Bro... What kinda girl is
your type, anyway?
144:
Huh? Really?! You're into the bald
ones?!
153: I see... I never knew that, Nimbus.
158:
What're we supposed to do? Dealing
with these is gonna be a huge pain!
162:
Let's think this through. Perhaps we
could claim to have the same
preferences as Nimbus does. That
would make a fine excuse to turn all
these offers down.
167:
Are you sure it's okay to make that
sort of info open to the public?
173:
Hold up! The hell are you two
planning?!
181:
A single-edged, 1.5 meter sword was
found in the Kaleidoscope. However,
it thoroughly reeked of fish. Why?
185:
Oh? Do you mean to say that some
terrible fool defiled a sword by using
it to prepare fish? A weapon of that
size deserves far more respect!
189:
I got it! It's not a sword, it's a knife!
One of those huge ones for cutting
up big ocean fish.
192:
Palpebra is landlocked and has no
need for those big fish knives, so the
adventurer assumed it must be a
sword! Right?
197:
Correct! You're quite brilliant with
answering these.
202:
Yay! I'm eating one of your
chocolates, Libram!
207:
Urk... The royal chocolates I had sent
from home...
211:
Wait... The question was phrased
dishonestly! You said it was a sword!
216:
You gotta think outside the box
more, Libram! A diplomat from the
Farlands can't be too hard-headed...
220:
Don't mock me, Black Cat. My skills
with people simply cannot match
my wealth.
228:
Whoa, it's Adjudicus! Hey, we're
doing a quiz battle and betting
snacks! Wanna join in?
232:
...I will pass. I did bring a souvenir,
though.
235:
This drink is a product of pure
madness—cursed, poisoned water
somehow turned into alcohol. I don't
know whether it would be to your
liking, however.
240:
Things are starting to get fun. Now
then, who will ask the next question?
253:
The Legend of Whitetail's author
sure was a genius...
256:
So much happened, but when he
took center stage like that... I... I...
259:
People will really believe whatever
they want...
273:
Thanks for waiting, everyone!
Nothing beats hot pot in the winter...
287:
Just the thing to help with a
hangover.
291:
Right? Warms you up, nice and
filling...
295:
Man, nothing beats ringing in the
new year with your friends!
